# Shekel Budget App -- Docker build context exclusions
#
# Closes audit finding F-113.  Goal: ship the smallest production
# image that still supports every container-side workflow documented
# in docs/runbook.md and entrypoint.sh.
#
# What MUST live inside the image:
#   - app/                      Flask application package
#   - migrations/               Alembic migration history (used by
#                               flask db upgrade in entrypoint.sh and
#                               docker exec ops)
#   - scripts/init_db.sql       Schema bootstrap (entrypoint.sh)
#   - scripts/init_db_role.sql  Role provisioning (entrypoint.sh)
#   - scripts/init_database.py  First-boot schema apply (entrypoint.sh)
#   - scripts/seed_user.py      Seed initial owner (entrypoint.sh +
#                               docker exec ops)
#   - scripts/seed_ref_tables.py    Seed lookup tables (entrypoint.sh)
#   - scripts/seed_tax_brackets.py  Seed US tax brackets (entrypoint.sh)
#   - scripts/seed_companion.py     Seed companion user (docker exec)
#   - scripts/audit_cleanup.py  Audit log retention (docker exec)
#   - scripts/integrity_check.py    Integrity sweep (docker exec)
#   - scripts/repair_orphaned_transfers.py    Data repair (docker exec)
#   - scripts/reset_mfa.py      Operator MFA reset (docker exec)
#   - scripts/rotate_sessions.py    Session invalidation (docker exec)
#   - scripts/rotate_totp_key.py    Key rotation (docker exec)
#   - alembic.ini               Alembic config
#   - entrypoint.sh             ENTRYPOINT
#   - gunicorn.conf.py          gunicorn config
#   - requirements.txt          Pip metadata reference (deps already
#                               built into /opt/venv in stage 1, but
#                               kept for forensic ``pip freeze``-style
#                               diffing inside a debugging exec)
#   - run.py                    Flask app factory entrypoint
#
# Everything else listed below is dev-time tooling, host-side ops
# scripts, build context noise, or documentation -- none of which is
# referenced from inside the container.

# ── Version control ────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore

# ── Environment & secrets ──────────────────────────────────────────
# .env files contain live credentials; never bake into the image.
# .env.example is exempted so the image carries the documentation
# template (referenced by docs/runbook_secrets.md procedures).
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Python build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg
*.egg-info
.eggs
build
dist

# ── Virtualenvs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .venv:        Developer virtualenv (deps already installed into
#               /opt/venv inside the image during stage 1).
# .audit-venv:  ~437 MB virtualenv used by the audit-time scanner
#               suite; host-only.
.venv
venv
env
.audit-venv

# ── Test infrastructure ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tests are not runnable inside the slim runtime image (no pytest, no
# test database fixtures); shipping them only inflates the layer.
tests/
.pytest_cache
htmlcov
.coverage
coverage.xml
pytest.ini

# ── Dev-only toolchain configs ─────────────────────────────────────
requirements-dev.txt
.pylintrc
.markdownlint.json
.rumdl.toml

# ── Logs & ephemeral state ─────────────────────────────────────────
# logs/ is a host-side directory used by deploy/backup scripts.  The
# app inside the container writes to stdout (captured by Docker's
# json-file driver per Commit C-15), never to /home/shekel/app/logs.
# state/ is created by entrypoint.sh when running under the dev
# compose's host-bind mount; the production image ships a fresh
# (empty) /home/shekel/app/state directory pre-created by the
# Dockerfile to anchor the named-volume mount.
logs/
pgdata/
state/
*.log

# ── Documentation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# docs/ holds runbooks, audit reports, plans, and design docs -- all
# operator-facing content.  The host-side checkout retains all of it
# for the operator; the runtime container does not need any of it.
# Top-level *.md files are the same story.
docs/
*.md

# ── Editor / IDE / OS ──────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── CI ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.github/

# ── Docker (don't include compose / Dockerfile in build context) ──
# Dockerfile and compose files are read by ``docker build`` and
# ``docker compose`` from the host; copying them into the image
# would only confuse a forensic reader and leak the deploy topology.
docker-compose*.yml
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# ── Deployment configs (mounted from host, not baked in) ───────────
# nginx configs under deploy/ are bind-mounted into the nginx
# container at runtime; the app container never reads them.  The
# compose override at deploy/docker-compose.prod.yml is consumed by
# ``docker compose`` on the host.  Audit finding F-021 / Commit C-32.
deploy/

# ── External service templates (host-side) ─────────────────────────
# cloudflared/config.yml is a template installed on the host as
# /etc/cloudflared/config.yml; it is not used by the app container.
cloudflared/

# ── Host-only diagnostics & monitoring ─────────────────────────────
diagnostics/
monitoring/

# ── Claude Code session state ──────────────────────────────────────
.claude/

# ── One-time patches (kept in repo for git history, not runtime) ───
amortization-fix.patch

# ── Worktrees / temp artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────
.worktrees/

# ── Dev-only scripts ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# scripts/ is mostly runtime-essential; entrypoint.sh runs five of
# the .py / .sql files at container start and the runbook documents
# many ``docker exec ... python scripts/...`` invocations.  Only the
# strictly host-only or build-time scripts are excluded here.
#
# scripts/audit/  Audit-time supporting modules (host-only).
# scripts/hooks/  Git / claude-code hooks (host-only).
# scripts/benchmark_triggers.py  Manual perf benchmark (dev-only;
#                 acceptable to run via host venv).
# scripts/vendor_google_fonts.py Vendoring step that runs at build
#                 time on the host; fonts already shipped in
#                 app/static/vendor/.
# scripts/backup.sh, restore.sh, verify_backup.sh,
# scripts/backup_retention.sh, deploy.sh, retire_stale_containers.sh
#                 Host-side ops scripts that talk to ``docker`` from
#                 outside the container.
# scripts/generate_pg_cert.sh
#                 Host-side cert generator (sudo, openssl) that
#                 produces deploy/postgres/server.{crt,key} for the
#                 shared-mode bind mount.  Runs once on the bare-metal
#                 host before ``docker compose up`` -- never executed
#                 inside the container.  Audit finding F-154 / Commit
#                 C-37.
scripts/audit/
scripts/hooks/
scripts/benchmark_triggers.py
scripts/vendor_google_fonts.py
scripts/backup.sh
scripts/backup_retention.sh
scripts/restore.sh
scripts/verify_backup.sh
scripts/deploy.sh
scripts/retire_stale_containers.sh
scripts/generate_pg_cert.sh
